<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width">
    <title>Sean Lange</title>
    <link href="/client/index/style.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" />
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Raleway&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto&display=swap" rel="stylesheet"> 
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Montserrat&display=swap" rel="stylesheet"> 
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Lato&display=swap" rel="stylesheet"> 
</head>
<body>
    <nav class="navigation" id="nav">
        <button id="homebutton">Home</button>
        <button id="projectbutton" onclick="location.href='projects'">Projects</button>
        <button id="contactbutton" onclick="location.href='contact'">Contact</button>
    </nav>
    <div class="top">
        <div class="starterContainer">
            <h1 id="name">Sean Lange</h1>
            <p id="saying">I enjoy programming in Typescript using Node.js and other JS frameworks for server-side applications.</p>
            <div class="buttonline">
                <button onclick="window.location='projects'">Projects</button>
                <button onclick="window.location='https://sean-lange.replit.app/client/media/resume.pdf'">Resume</button>
                <button onclick="window.location='contact'">Contact</button>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="links">
            <% for(let name in projects.links) { let link = projects.links[name] %>
                <img src="/images/<%= link.image %>" onclick="window.location='<%= link.link %>'" alt=<%= name %> />
            <% } %>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="content" id="content">
        <div id="divbreakgrad"></div>
        <div id="whitediagonal"></div>

        <div class="aboutme">
            <p>I am an upcoming freshman at the University of South Florida, and have been programming for 6 years. I originally started programming in the summer before 7th grade when I wanted to create a Pi calculator in Python. This project was very simple, however in finishing it, I felt a feeling of joy that propelled me to improve and learn about coding and its applications.<br><br>In the past, I have made games using the HTML canvas, and since the end of 2019, have been focused on building web applications using Node.js and typescript as a backend. I am highly proficient with Javascript, and also have experience programming in Python, Java, Dart, and Rust.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="projects">
            <h2 class="title"><b>Projects</b></h2>
            <div class="indivprojects">
                <% for(let name of projects.highlights) { let project = projects.projects[name] %>
                    <div class="project" onclick="window.open('<%= project.link %>'), '_blank'">
                        <img src="/images/<%= project.image %>" class="projectimage" draggable="false">
                        <h2 class="ptitle"><%= name %></h2>
                        <div class="pwords">
                            <p><%= project.description %></p>
                            <div class="pbuttons">
                            <button onclick="window.open('<%= project.code %>');">View Code</button>
                            <button onclick="window.open('<%= project.link %>');">View Project</button>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                <% } %>
            </div>
            <div class="allprojects">
                <button onclick="location.href='projects'">More Projects</button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <script src="/client/index/script.js"></script>
</body>